column1: When an rsocks.net service user buys a plan, it must be activated for a single source IP address representing the user'

After setting the source IP address, the package rental period can be started and paused a number of times, depending on the plan, but daily or hourly packages cannot be paused. The service permits using the acquired pool of proxies during the period, switching a fraction of proxies within the pool every two hours. Twenty-four hours later, the user can manually switch the entire pool of addresses for new ones.&nbsp
